<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-06-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-06-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="277" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d277">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-06-01"><hi rend="italic">June 1,
                            1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>(Mr. Rockhill reports a rapid reduction of the military forces of the powers
                        in consequence of the acceptance by the Emperor of China of the amount of
                        the indemnity at 450,000,000 taels and the rate of interest at 4 per cent.
                        The German forces will be reduced to one brigade, and Count Waldersee has
                        received orders to return immediately to Germany).</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>